Fresh Pi session: REPAIR ONLY CURRENT ACTIONABLE FINDINGS.

Inputs:
- Latest deterministic validation issues under {{run.dir}}/validation/, if any
- Latest review issues under {{run.dir}}/review/, if any
- Design and scenario inventory: {{run.dir}}/design/ and {{run.dir}}/test-list/
- Worktree: {{run.worktree-dir}}

Goal:
Resolve the newest current findings with the smallest coherent change and return to deterministic regression.

Rules:
- Use only the newest applicable validation and review issue files; older reports are historical context, not an accumulated backlog.
- Confirm each finding still reproduces before editing. Do not repair obsolete prose.
- Fix current code, tests, documentation, or metadata as required without weakening assertions or broadening scope.
- Do not fabricate or reconstruct historical red evidence. If a current behavior lacks coverage, write a new `scenarios-{{run.round}}-repair.json` snapshot that adds or reopens one pending scenario (within the eight-scenario cap) so the normal focused loop can address it; do not claim it was previously red.
- Run focused checks while repairing, preserve unrelated validated work, and commit a coherent repair when checks pass.
- Do not push or create a PR.

Write:
- Summary: {{run.dir}}/repair/summary-{{run.round}}.md
- Updated scenario snapshot when coverage work is needed: {{run.dir}}/test-list/scenarios-{{run.round}}-repair.json
- Status: {{run.dir}}/repair/status-{{run.round}}.json
- Remaining current issues on failure only: {{run.dir}}/repair/issues-{{run.round}}.json

Statuses:
{"status":"pass","summary":"current findings repaired","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"current repair remains incomplete","issues_file":"repair/issues-{{run.round}}.json"}
